! Built-in keys

|!Key |!Effect |
|`Ctrl-Space` |Open / reset palette |
|`Tab` |Cycle focus section |
|`Shift-Tab` |Reverse cycle focus |
|`↑` `↓` |Move row selection |
|`→` |Drill (same as Tab on row) |
|`←` |Pop one stage |
|`↵` |Fire selected row |
|`Ctrl-↵` |Fire + keep palette open |
|`Space` |Toggle / edit / open action menu on row |
|`Esc` |Pop stage; from root, close |
|`Shift-Esc` |Close palette outright |
|`DEL` |Remove focused pill / reset row to default |
|`Ctrl-DEL` |Clear all pills in focused strip |
|`Ctrl-↑` `Ctrl-↓` |Reorder row (when row declares move actions) |
|hold `Ctrl` |Show row detail drawer |

! Leaders (registered live)

The cascade keeps the input focused while you type a leader key — once you stop typing (idle window, default 500ms), the leader fires. Plugins can register new leaders; the table below reflects what's currently in the wiki.

